      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(copilot): drop thinking blocks from replay",
        "body": "## Summary\n- strip thinking blocks from GitHub Copilot Claude replay history instead of preserving the latest assistant reasoning turn\n- apply the same Copilot Claude stripping rule to the request-time Anthropic stream payload wrapper used for tool continuations\n- replace thinking-only Copilot Claude assistant replay payloads with a non-empty omitted-reasoning assistant text block so Anthropic turn shape remains valid\n- keep the existing default latest-assistant preservation behavior for other providers/callers\n- cover Copilot replay cases for text, thinking-only turns, tool calls, and request-time payload replay\n\nFixes #81520\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed:\nGitHub Copilot Claude should not receive prior assistant `thinking` or `redacted_thinking` blocks when OpenClaw replays session history or sends a tool-continuation request payload, because Copilot rejects those replayed blocks.\n\nReal environment tested:\nWSL2 Ubuntu checkout at `/home/giodl/src/openclaw-85529`, PR head `0c647f5cade6026dedb72975d6cbbb57d80df3db`, source-level runtime payload harness through the real `wrapCopilotAnthropicStream` request wrapper, plus focused embedded-agent replay tests. Prior redacted live Copilot Claude proof exists on old head `f31f6c771a1` and still covers the same provider send path; this refresh only rebases on current main and changes thinking-only payload replay from dropping the assistant turn to preserving a neutral omitted-reasoning text turn.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts extensions/github-copilot/provider-runtime.contract.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n2. `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/github-copilot/stream.ts extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/replay-history.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts`\n3. `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/github-copilot/stream.ts extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/replay-history.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts`\n4. `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n5. `git diff --check`\n6. `/home/giodl/.local/toolchains/node-v22.22.3-linux-x64/bin/codex review --base origin/main`\n\nEvidence after fix:\nVitest output: 5 files passed, 115 tests passed on refreshed head. Formatter output: all matched files use the correct format. Oxlint output: found 0 warnings and 0 errors. Diff whitespace checks produced no output. Codex review found no discrete regression after the thinking-only payload shape fix. The `wrapCopilotAnthropicStream` regression tests capture the real outgoing Copilot Anthropic payload after `options.onPayload` and assert mixed assistant content is reduced to visible text while thinking-only assistant replay messages become `[assistant reasoning omitted]` text before tool-result continuation replay.\n\nObserved result after fix:\nThe request-time Copilot Anthropic payload wrapper now removes both `thinking` and `redacted_thinking` assistant content before applying cache markers. A tool-continuation payload with a thinking-only assistant replay message keeps the assistant turn as a non-empty omitted-reasoning text message, while surrounding user and tool-result messages remain intact.\n\nWhat was not tested:\nA fresh live Copilot Claude run on rebased head `0c647f5cad` was not available in this WSL environment. Prior redacted live proof on `f31f6c771a1` showed an authenticated Copilot Claude request with `payloadContainsThinking: false` and a successful response on the same provider path.\n\n## Validation\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts extensions/github-copilot/provider-runtime.contract.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 5 files, 115 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/github-copilot/stream.ts extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/replay-history.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/github-copilot/stream.ts extensions/github-copilot/stream.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/replay-history.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/thinking.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.sanitize-session-history.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `git log --show-signature --format=\"%h %G? %s\" origin/main..HEAD` -> both commits have good signatures\n- `/home/giodl/.local/toolchains/node-v22.22.3-linux-x64/bin/codex review --base origin/main` -> no findings\n\nNo public config, plugin API, CLI flag, env var, migration, or plugin contract surface was added.",
